  "commentary": "With SPX at 6595.42 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6590 (-10.3B) and positive gamma wall at 6605 (+14.5B), dealers are caught in a critical hedging zone where they must buy any dip toward 6590 and sell any rally toward 6605. The recent regime flip into BREAKOUT mode with -4.8B total GEX means dealers are amplifying moves away from this tight range, creating a coiled spring effect. Watch for explosive moves if we break below 6590 (dealers accelerate buying) or above 6605 (dealers accelerate selling), with 6580 and 6610 as the next major GEX walls.\n\nBottom line: expect violent moves in either direction once we break out of the narrow 6590-6605 range.",
